posts.description:
One of my favourite japanese traditional sweets is none other than Castella Cake. I like to eat the skin of the cake, especially. It felt nostalgic,  always , and the feelings missed to touch one's heart.

Here, wagashi master Masaaki Miyake has combined his skills in sculpturing mini animal shaped nerikiri with his castella cake. It is an interesting way to present a cake to your family members and guests. Even a sick patient would wake up smelling the cakes (just as Kamado Tanjiro did from Demon Slayer 😅) @kimetsu_movie_campaign

Would you like to learn how to make castella cake from the expert ?

Master Miyake will be bringing his expertise in his first japanese confectionery masterclass (hands-on) in SINGAPORE 2025! 

Stay tuned to our page for the class details and registration announcement. Registration will start very, very soon!

